attacks.name: Flamebody Cannon
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon, and this attack also does 90 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: This Pokémon's power level rises along with the temperature of its fire, which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

data.name: Pelipper
data.flavorText: It protects its young in its beak. It bobs on waves, resting on them on days when the waters are calm.

data.name: Remoraid

attacks.name: Flail
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

data.name: Wingull
data.flavorText: It rides upon ocean winds as if it were a glider. In the winter, it hides food around its nest.

data.name: Octillery

attacks.name: Aqua Wash
attacks.text: You may put an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon into their hand.

attacks.name: Octo Beatdown
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 90 damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

data.name: Lombre

attacks.name: Aqua Slash
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

data.flavorText: Old folklore in Kitakami tells of a mischievous child who was reborn as a Pokémon.

data.name: Ludicolo

abilities.name: Vibrant Dance
abilities.text: All of your Pokémon in play get +40 HP. The effect of Vibrant Dance doesn't stack.

data.flavorText: There are structures throughout its whole body that produce energy when hit by sound waves with a cheerful rhythm.

data.name: Articuno

attacks.name: Frigid Fluttering
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Water Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon can control ice at will. Articuno is said to live in snowy mountains riddled with permafrost.

data.name: Lotad
data.flavorText: The leaf on its head is naturally dirt repellent and will stay clean even after transporting Pokémon that are covered in mud.

data.name: Veluza ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Purging Strike
attacks.text: You may discard your hand. If you discarded any cards in this way, this attack does 120 more damage.

data.name: Wailmer
data.flavorText: When it sucks in a large volume of seawater, it becomes like a big, bouncy ball. It eats a ton of food daily.

data.name: Alolan Geodude
data.flavorText: If you step on a Geodude sleeping on the ground, you'll hear a zapping sound and feel a tingling shock throughout your entire body.

data.name: Alolan Golem

attacks.name: Electromagnetic Catapult
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Megaton Fall
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 40 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: It fires rocks charged with electricity. Even if the rock isn't fired that accurately, just grazing an opponent will cause numbness and fainting.

data.name: Iono's Voltorb

attacks.name: Voltaic Chain
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Lightning Energy attached to all of your Iono's Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

data.name: Iono's Electrode

attacks.name: Thump-Thump Boom
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 100 damage to itself. Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is Knocked Out.

data.flavorText: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

data.name: N's Joltik

attacks.name: Zapping Short
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon. If you discarded a Pokémon Tool in this way, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: Since it can't generate its own electricity, it sticks onto large-bodied Pokémon and absorbs static electricity.

data.name: Alolan Graveler
data.flavorText: Graveler's entire body is electrically charged due to the stones it likes to eat. It is a very quick-tempered Pokémon.

data.name: Wailord

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Its immense size is the reason for its popularity. Wailord watching is a favorite sightseeing activity in various parts of the world.

data.name: Regice

attacks.name: Blizzard
attacks.text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: With cold air that can reach temperatures as low as −328 degrees Fahrenheit, Regice instantly freezes any creature that approaches it.

data.name: Togedemaru

attacks.name: Toge Spark
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

data.name: Tapu Koko ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Linked Lightning
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

data.name: Iono's Bellibolt ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Electric Streamer
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Basic Lightning Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Iono's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Thunderous Bolt
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

data.name: Iono's Wattrel

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

data.flavorText: When its wings catch the wind, the bones within produce electricity. This Pokémon dives into the ocean, catching prey by electrocuting them.

data.name: Mr. Mime

attacks.name: Mimic
attacks.text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw a card for each card in your opponent's hand.

attacks.name: Psy Bolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: It's known for its top-notch pantomime skills. It protects itself from all sorts of attacks by emitting auras from its fingers to create walls.

data.name: Beldum
data.flavorText: The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground's natural magnetism, letting it float.

data.name: Iono's Tadbulb
data.flavorText: Tadbulb shakes its tail to generate electricity. If it senses danger, it will make its head blink on and off to alert its allies.

data.name: Iono's Kilowattrel

abilities.name: Flashing Draw
abilities.text: You must discard a Basic Lightning Energy from this Pokémon in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

data.flavorText: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.

data.name: Lillie's Clefairy ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Fairy Zone
abilities.text: The Weakness of each of your opponent's Dragon Pokémon in play is now Psychic. (Apply Weakness as ×2.)

attacks.name: Full Moon Rondo
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

data.name: Alolan Marowak

attacks.name: Retaliate
attacks.text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon sets the bone it holds on fire and dances through the night as a way to mourn its fallen allies.

data.name: Shuppet
data.flavorText: It loves to feed on feelings like envy and malice. Its upright horn catches the emotions of people.

data.name: Banette

attacks.name: Cursed Words
attacks.text: Your opponent chooses 3 cards from their hand and shuffles those cards into their deck.

data.flavorText: This Pokémon developed from an abandoned doll that amassed a grudge. It is seen in dark alleys.

data.name: Metang
data.flavorText: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its two brains are linked, amplifying its psychic power.

data.name: Lillie's Cutiefly

attacks.name: Hold Still
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: When it senses the auras of people or Pokémon who are having fun, it will draw close and give them a painful poke with its long proboscis.

data.name: Lillie's Comfey

attacks.name: Inviting Flowers
attacks.text: You may search your deck for any number of Basic Lillie's Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Fade Out
attacks.text: Put this Pokémon and all attached cards into your hand.

data.flavorText: It uses its vine to pick flowers. The flowers that Comfey attaches to itself develop healing properties.
